# Architecture Rules

## File Size Limit

**No file may exceed 250 lines of code.** If a file approaches this limit, extract logic into smaller modules immediately.

## Separation of Concerns

| Layer | Location | Responsibility |
|----|----|---|
| Presentational Components (shared) | `src/components/{atoms,molecules,organisms}/` | Render UI only. Same structure on all surfaces. No business logic, no API calls, no complex state. |
| Presentational Components (desktop-only) | `src/components/desktop/{atoms,molecules,organisms}/` | Web-desktop-only UI. Composed behind `useAppSurface()` / screen entry. |
| Presentational Components (PWA / mobile-native) | `src/components/pwa/{atoms,molecules,organisms}/` | Mobile / standalone PWA-only UI. Touch-first, safe-area aware. Composed behind `useAppSurface()` / screen entry. |
| Custom Hooks | `src/hooks/` | Business logic, API calls, state management. Named `useFeature.ts`. |
| Server Actions | `src/app/**/actions.ts` | Supabase mutations, email sending, server-side validation. |
| Lib / Services | `src/lib/` | Client initialization, utilities, parsers. Pure functions preferred. |
| Types | `src/types/` | Shared TypeScript interfaces and type definitions. |

## Component Rules

1. Components receive data via **props** and communicate via **callbacks**. No direct service calls inside components.
2. Each component is a **named export** in its own file. One component per file.
3. Props interfaces are defined in the same file, co-located above the component.
4. Use `'use client'` directive only when the component genuinely needs browser APIs or interactivity. Default to Server Components.

## Hook Rules

1. Each hook manages one cohesive concern (e.g., `useLogin`, `useEnrollment`).
2. Hooks return a typed object: `{ data, error, isLoading, handlers }`.
3. External dependencies (Supabase client, router) are injected or imported from `src/lib/`.
